PORT=3000

# Primary database configuration (used by app)
DB_HOST=localhost
DB_PORT=3306
DB_USER=root
DB_PASSWORD=yourpassword
DB_NAME=kompi_cyber

# Team member's nextgen database
TEAM_DB_HOST=localhost
TEAM_DB_PORT=3306
TEAM_DB_USER=root
TEAM_DB_PASSWORD=theirpassword
TEAM_DB_NAME=nextgen
# Your own database
YOUR_DB_HOST=localhost
YOUR_DB_PORT=3306
YOUR_DB_USER=root
YOUR_DB_PASSWORD=yourpassword
YOUR_DB_NAME=my_auth_db

JWT_SECRET=make_this_a_long_random_string
JWT_EXPIRES_IN=1d
```

---

## How to test (use Postman or Thunder Client in VS Code)
```
# Login
POST  http://localhost:3000/api/auth/login
Body (JSON): { "email": "user@example.com", "password": "abc123" }

# Get my profile (copy token from login response)
GET   http://localhost:3000/api/auth/me
Header: Authorization: Bearer <paste_token_here>

# Logout
POST  http://localhost:3000/api/auth/logout
Header: Authorization: Bearer <paste_token_here>